+# Flesch readability (SF parity) + Playwright E2E harness — Implementation Plan
+
+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
+
+**Goal:** Move slice 2.1 (Flesch readability) from "FK Grade today" to "SF Reading Ease, persisted, exposed through API + UI, verified via Playwright crawl of boltrack.in" — and along the way stand up the workspace's first Playwright E2E harness.
+
+**Architecture:** Pure-math `readability` module in `sf-core` (zero IO deps, per CODING_STANDARDS). Parser computes the score during HTML parse; pipeline writes `readability_score` + `readability_bucket` to `crawl_urls`. Evaluator reads from the row instead of recomputing. API surfaces the new fields. UI renders a Content tab with a readability badge tagged with `data-testid` for Playwright. New `e2e/` workspace runs Playwright against the running stack.
+
+**Tech Stack:** Rust + sqlx + Axum (existing) · React 18 + Vite + Tailwind + shadcn (existing) · Playwright + TypeScript (new) · Postgres + Redis via docker-compose (existing).
