+## Subagent dispatch pattern
+
+Each slice is one Agent call with `isolation: "worktree"`. The prompt template lives at `templates/subagent-prompt-template.md`. Parallel fan-out = multiple Agent calls in one message. Sequential = chain by dependency from the inventory's `Blocks` column.
+
+Branch naming: `{type}/{slice-id}-{kebab-name}` — e.g. `feat/2-1-flesch-readability`.
+
+Commit style: conventional commits (matches existing history). One logical change per commit.
+
+PR template: `templates/pr-template.md`. Each PR title is `{type}({scope}): {message}` and the body includes:
+- Link to the slice's master-spec row
+- Link to the sub-project spec
+- Acceptance criterion verbatim
+- Test commands run + their output
+- Status emoji change (e.g. `❌ → ✅`) for the inventory row
+
+After a slice merges, the master spec's inventory row is updated in a follow-up commit (or by the same PR if simple).
+
+## E2E test harness
+
+`e2e/` at workspace root. TypeScript + `@playwright/test`. Drives the deployed UI through real browser sessions.
+
+- `playwright.config.ts` — baseURL `http://localhost:80` (your nginx port), override via `E2E_BASE_URL`
+- Auth via existing `SF_DEV_MODE=1` token mint
+- One `*.spec.ts` per slice that has UI-visible behavior
+- Smoke spec (`e2e/tests/smoke.spec.ts`) — "UI loads, status footer shows version" — must pass before any other E2E
+
+Test pattern per slice (e.g. Flesch):
+1. UI loads, project created, crawl on `boltrack.in` started with max-pages 30
+2. Poll `/v1/crawls/:id` until `status=completed` (timeout 5 min)
+3. Navigate UI to Content tab → URL detail
+4. Assert readability column populated, bucket label visible
+
+`freshprintsupply.ca` is used as a secondary smoke (different project, multi-tenant isolation check).
+
+`e2e/README.md` documents local run, CI run, debugging.
+
+## CI integration
+
+- Existing `.github/workflows/ci.yml` extended with `e2e` job: spin up `docker-compose.yml` services, install Playwright, run `npm --prefix e2e run e2e`
+- E2E job runs against `main` and PR branches; failures block merge
+- Cache `~/.cache/ms-playwright` for browser binaries
+
